---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const siteUrl = 'https://aicostplanner.com';
const currentDate = new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0];
const route = '/image-generation-api-cost/';
const breadcrumbs = [{ label: 'Image Generation API Cost', href: route }];
const internalLinks = [
  { href: '/image-generation-api-pricing/', label: 'Image Generation API Pricing' },
  { href: '/gpt-image-api-cost/', label: 'GPT Image API Cost' },
  { href: '/gpt-image-api-pricing/', label: 'GPT Image API Pricing' },
  { href: '/failed-generation-cost/', label: 'Failed Generation Cost' },
  { href: '/billing-transparency/', label: 'Billing Transparency' },
];
---

<PageLayout
  title="Image Generation API Cost Guide"
  description="Understand image generation API cost across generated images, edits, image-to-image, quality settings, retries and usage review."
  canonical={`${siteUrl}${route}`}
  type="article"
  lastUpdated={currentDate}
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Article",
      "headline": "Image Generation API Cost: Generated Images, Edits and Quality Settings",
      "description": "Understand image generation API cost across generated images, edits, image-to-image, quality settings, retries and usage review.",
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "AICostPlanner" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "AICostPlanner", "url": siteUrl },
      "datePublished": currentDate,
      "dateModified": currentDate,
      "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `${siteUrl}${route}` }
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": siteUrl },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Image Generation API Cost", "item": `${siteUrl}${route}` }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="hero-dark"><div class="container"><Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} /><h1 class="page-title">Image Generation API Cost</h1><p class="page-meta"><span class="label-mono">Last updated: {currentDate}</span></p></div></section>
    <section class="section-light content-section"><div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="quick-answer"><h2>Quick Answer</h2><p>Image generation API cost can depend on generated image count, edits, image-to-image workflows, quality settings, resolution and retry behavior. Provider billing policy determines whether failed requests affect your bill.</p></div>
      <h2>What affects cost</h2><p>Image cost changes with the number of generated images, edit or variation requests, image-to-image input handling, output resolution, quality tier and whether retries or moderation failures are counted in the bill.</p>
      <h2>Common billing units</h2><ul><li><span class="mono">image</span> for generated output count</li><li><span class="mono">edit</span> for inpainting or editing operations</li><li><span class="mono">resolution</span> as a cost multiplier</li><li><span class="mono">quality</span> for HD or detail-enhanced output</li></ul>
      <h2>Cost risks</h2><p>Retries for failed generations, moderation-filtered outputs, batch processing and unexpected resolution defaults can all make actual spend diverge from initial estimates.</p>
      <h2>Small test checklist</h2><ul class="checklist"><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Generate one small batch first</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Record request IDs and output counts</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Test edits and image-to-image separately</span></li><li><span class="checklist-icon">&#10003;</span><span>Check whether failed or retried jobs were billed</span></li></ul>
      <h2>Common errors / failed tasks</h2>      <p>Moderation filtering, invalid parameters, retry loops, resolution mismatches and duplicate requests can all affect billed usage. Use logs to compare against dashboard records.</p>

      <!-- New: Megapixels, image size and image generation cost -->
      <h2>Megapixels, Image Size and Image Generation Cost</h2>
      <p>
        Some image API cost models may depend on generated image count, dimensions, megapixels, quality,
        edits, image-to-image inputs, retries or provider-specific billing policy. Not all providers
        bill purely by image count—dimensions and megapixels can be a cost multiplier.
      </p>
      <p>
        To estimate image API cost safely without forcing everything into token-language:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Choose one model and note its pricing basis (per image, per megapixel, or per resolution tier)</li>
        <li>Choose one image size or quality level to test</li>
        <li>Run one small test request and record the <span class="mono">request_id</span></li>
        <li>Compare your provider's usage record against the request ID</li>
        <li>Scale slowly, testing each new size or quality tier before adding volume</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Some providers bill higher resolutions as multiple images or as a megapixel multiplier.
        Image-to-image workflows that send a reference image may incur additional input charges.
        Moderation-filtered or failed requests may or may not be billed depending on the provider's policy.
        For a comparison of how different models handle pricing units, see
        <a href="/image-generation-api-pricing/">Image Generation API Pricing</a>.
        For GPT-specific image cost patterns, see
        <a href="/gpt-image-api-pricing/">GPT Image API Pricing</a>.
        For understanding billed vs. unbilled failures, see
        <a href="/failed-generation-cost/">Failed Generation Cost</a>.
        For reconciling usage against billing records, see
        <a href="/billing-transparency/">Billing Transparency</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Related pages</h2><div class="link-cards">{internalLinks.map(link => (<a href={link.href} class="link-card"><h4>{link.label}</h4><p>Read the related image cost or pricing topic</p></a>))}</div>
      <div class="ai-summary-block"><div class="ai-summary-label"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4M12 8h.01"/></svg> AI Summary</div><p>Image generation API cost can depend on generated image count, edits, image-to-image, resolution, quality settings and retry behavior. This page is educational and helps developers review workflow-level spend. Check live provider pricing before production use and test small before scaling.</p></div>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Is image API cost always per image?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Often yes, but providers may also vary cost by edit type, image-to-image mode, resolution or quality settings.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Can failed image requests affect spend?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Depending on provider billing policy, yes. Use logs to confirm.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">Should I test quality settings separately?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Yes. Running one test at standard quality and one at HD helps you see the cost difference before scaling.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3 class="faq-question">How do megapixels or image size affect image API cost?</h3><p class="faq-answer">Some providers bill by megapixel or resolution tier rather than by image count alone. Higher resolutions, HD quality settings, or detail-enhanced outputs may cost more per image. Image-to-image workflows that include a reference image input may also add input-side charges. Testing at one size or quality level before scaling helps you understand the actual cost basis.</p></div></div>
      <div class="cta-block"><h3>Start with a small prepaid test</h3><p>Create an API key with $1 trial credit and test image generation cost before scaling.</p><div class="cta-buttons"><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/register?lng=en" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create API Key <span class="btn-subtext">$1 trial credit</span></a><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/pricing" class="btn btn-secondary-dark" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Compare Model Pricing</a><a href="https://app.rutaapi.com/register?lng=en" class="btn btn-secondary-dark" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Start with a Small Prepaid Test</a></div></div>
    </div></section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .hero-dark { background: var(--color-bg-dark); padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-10); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-bg-dark-border); }
  .hero-dark :global(.breadcrumb) { margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
  .page-title { font-size: 2.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text-dark); line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) 0; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .page-meta { margin: 0; }
  .content-section { padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-16); background: var(--color-bg-light); }
  .quick-answer { background: var(--color-bg-light-elevated); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-blue); padding: var(--space-6); border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0; margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .quick-answer h2 { font-size: 1.125rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .quick-answer p { margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-light); line-height: 1.7; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4); padding-top: var(--space-6); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; border-top: none; }
  p { color: var(--color-text-light-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  ul, ol { color: var(--color-text-light-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); padding-left: var(--space-6); }
  li { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); line-height: 1.7; }
  .mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.875em; background: var(--color-bg-light-muted); padding: 0.125em 0.375em; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .checklist { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .checklist li { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: var(--space-3); padding: var(--space-3) 0; }
  .checklist-icon { color: var(--color-accent-green); font-weight: bold; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .link-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
  .link-card { display: block; padding: var(--space-5); background: var(--color-bg-light-elevated); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); text-decoration: none; transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .link-card:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent-blue); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .link-card h4 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0; }
  .link-card p { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-light-muted); margin: 0; }
  .ai-summary-block { background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.04), rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.04)); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.15); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); padding: var(--space-6); margin: var(--space-10) 0; }
  .ai-summary-label { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--color-accent-cyan); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .ai-summary-block p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.8; }
  .faq-list { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .faq-item { padding: var(--space-6) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); }
  .faq-question { font-size: 1.0625rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .faq-answer { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .cta-block { text-align: center; padding: var(--space-10); background: var(--color-bg-light-muted); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); margin-top: var(--space-10); }
  .cta-block h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cta-block p { max-width: 40ch; margin: 0 auto var(--space-6); }
  .cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: var(--space-4); justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-blue), var(--color-accent-cyan)); color: white; padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .btn-primary:hover { transform: translateY(-1px); box-shadow: 0 4px 12px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.3); color: white; }
  .btn-subtext { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; opacity: 0.9; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); }
  .btn-secondary-dark { background: transparent; color: var(--color-text-light); padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6); border-radius: var(--radius-md); font-weight: 500; border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-2); transition: all var(--transition-fast); }
  .btn-secondary-dark:hover { border-color: var(--color-accent-blue); color: var(--color-accent-blue); }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .page-title { font-size: 1.75rem; } .link-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; } .cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; justify-content: center; } }
</style>
